train = (Auto$year%%2 == 0)  # if the year is even
test = !train
Auto.train = Auto[train, ]
Auto.test = Auto[test, ]
mpg01.test = Auto.test$mpg01
library(MASS)
lda.fit = lda(mpg01 ~ acceleration + weight + displacement +cylinders , data = Auto.train)
lda.pred = predict(lda.fit, Auto.test)
mean(lda.pred$class != mpg01.test)

p(x)=exp{Bo+B1X}/(1+exp{Bo+B1X}) 1-exp{Bo+B1X}/(1+exp{Bo+B1X})=exp{Bo+B1X}/(1+exp{Bo+B1X}) p(x)=exp{Bo+B1X}/(1+exp{Bo+B1X})/(1-exp{Bo+B1X}/(1+exp{Bo+B1X})) p(x)=exp{Bo+B1X}/(1+exp{Bo+B1X})/(1/(1+exp{Bo+B1X})) p(x)/(1-p(x))=exp{Bo+B1X}/(1+exp{Bo+B1X})

4.7.8

For KNN with k=1, the training error rate will always be 0%. Therefore, a KNN with an average error rate of 18% between training and test will have a test error rate of 36%. Since were looking for the method with the lowest test error rate, I would choose the logistic regression, since its error rate of 30% is lower.
